Israel Hayom Exposed: A Glimpse of the Assaf Facility
Popular terrorism focuses on harming civilians and aims to undermine the sense of security necessary for the proper conduct of the civilian population.
The severe wave of terror attacks that took place this year, with attacks in Beersheba, Hadera, Bnei Brak, Ariel and Elad, and especially the one that took place in early April on the busy Dizengoff Street in the heart of Tel Aviv, by a terrorist who was assimilated into the crowd, led the police to think creatively in order to develop a tool that could be used to train fighters to attack terrorists within the civilian population.
The work of thinking was led by the Training Division of the Police and the Border Police.
They participated in a competition in the various police districts under the title "Commanders Leading Learning", in which each district was required to develop measures that would help improve the policing and combat skills of the fighters, policemen and commanders.
